Build bookworm-gnome sdcard for raspberrypi5:

Input files: ../rootfs-bookworm/linaro-esp.img
             ../rootfs-bookworm/linaro-rootfs.img

cd ~/Downloads
wget https://github.com/worproject/rpi5-uefi/releases/download/v0.3/RPi5_UEFI_Release_v0.3.zip

cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/bookworm-gnome

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
sudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/RPi5_UEFI_Release_v0.3.zip -o/mnt && sync && sudo umount /mnt
Eject sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to rpi5.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sync
free
Check CPU speed:
cat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu0/cpufreq/scaling_cur_freq

Check fan:
cat /proc/device-tree/cooling_fan/status
cat /sys/class/thermal/cooling_device0/type

glxinfo | grep OpenGL
dpkg -l | grep mesa
date
Check if Debian is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc firefox-esr vlc vlc-plugin-video-output

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 0 as default )

firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan-temp.mp4 --merge-output-format mp4 && ffmpeg -hide_banner -loglevel error -i swan-temp.mp4 -c:v libx265 -pix_fmt yuv420p -crf 28 -preset faster -c:a copy swan.mp4   ( It may take 15 minutes )

mpv --hwdec=auto-copy swan.mp4
ffplay swan.mp4
cvlc --gl=wgl --glconv=any swan.mp4

Plugin ASUS USB-BT500 bluetooth usb dongle to rpi5.
sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
